defaultBIG
default), and represented a major new source of funding for asset-based community development in 
defaultrural Scotland by providing a new mechanism to support ownership activities along with the Land Reform (Scotland) Act 2003 ('the Act'). It was administered by Highlands and Islands Enterprise (
defaultHIE
default) in partnership with Scottish Enterprise, and delivered thr
defaultough
default&#xa0;
defaultHIE
default's Community Land Unit.
default&#xa0;
